commit.message: README.rst: Add note about looking for maintainers
setup.py: Set url to my git repo

Add ability to get version from git tags (#9)

if `setup` is called with `use_vcs_version=True`, then the version is
obtained by doing `git describe --tags --dirty`.

Optimize directory scanning to skip ignored directories (#12)

This avoids walking possibly large folders like node_modules, which becomes
especially important when working on NFS or shared-folder mounts.

Return early if a directory isn't managed by git (#10)

This makes things much faster for large non-git trees that happen to
have setuptools_git among their indirect requirements.  For example,
this takes Launchpad's "python setup.py egg_info" from 16 seconds to 2
seconds for me.
